# our-table — Project Overview

## Architecture

Browser (React + TS) → FastAPI backend → PostgreSQL, recipe-scrapers, Google/GitHub OAuth

- Backend: `backend/app/` — FastAPI, SQLAlchemy async, Alembic, Authlib
- Frontend: `frontend/src/` — React 18, TypeScript, Vite, TanStack Query, Tailwind, shadcn/ui
- Local infra: `docker-compose.yml` (Postgres on 5432), `docker-compose.test.yml` (test DB on 5433)

## DB Models

| Model | Key Columns |
|---|---|
| `users` | id, email, name, avatar_url, oauth_provider, oauth_sub, flavor_profile (JSONB), created_at |
| `source_recipes` | id, url (unique), title, description, ingredients (JSONB), instructions (JSONB), image_url, servings, extracted_at |
| `user_recipes` | id, user_id (FK), source_recipe_id (FK), title, ingredients (JSONB), instructions (JSONB), notes, image_url, servings, created_at, updated_at |
| `recipe_shares` | id, user_recipe_id (FK), slug (unique), created_at |

`source_recipes` stores original scraped content; user edits live only in `user_recipes`.
For copyright reasons, extractor logic does not scrape/store source-site images; users can upload their own image, otherwise the frontend shows a default fallback image.

## Key API Endpoints

- `POST /api/recipes/extract` — scrape URL (text fields only; no source-image capture); return source_recipe + duplicate detection
- `POST /api/recipes/source/{id}/save` — create user_recipes copy
- `GET /api/recipes/mine` — list user's saved recipes
- `GET/PUT /api/recipes/mine/{id}` — fetch / update a user recipe
- `POST /api/recipes/mine/{id}/image` — upload a user-owned recipe image
- `POST /api/recipes/mine/{id}/share` — generate public share slug (P2)
- `GET /api/shared/{slug}` — public share page (P2)
- `GET /api/auth/google|github`, `GET /api/auth/callback/{provider}` — OAuth flow
- `GET /api/users/me`, `PUT /api/users/me/flavor-profile` — user profile

## Feature Priorities

- **P0**: URL extraction, save/edit recipe, title/ingredients/instructions/notes editable, original preserved
- **P1**: Duplicate detection (409 on re-save same URL, override allowed)
- **P2**: Public share links, flavor profile

## Conventions

- All routes are prefixed `/api/`
- Auth: JWT stored in cookie via `js-cookie`; backend validates on every protected route
- Error responses: `{"detail": "..."}` (FastAPI default)
- Tests are written alongside every feature — never after
